## More modification to lexical analyzer

Change identifier. Some number of letters + digits:
    - first digit is even then even number of digits
    - first digit is odd then odd number of digits
{LETTER}+(([13579]{DIGIT}({DIGIT}{DIGIT})*)|([02468]({DIGIT}{DIGIT})*))    std::cout << "T_ID: " << YYText() << std::endl;


if two rules match first one has prio.

# multiline comments:
/*     */

version1: only letters and whitespaces inside
"/*"[ \n\t\ra-zA-Z]*"*/"   std::cout << "T_MULTILINECOMMENT" << std::endl;

version2: anything except * sign
"/*"[^*]*"*/"   std::cout << "T_MULTILINECOMMENT" << std::endl;

version3: everything is accepted
[Automaton](data:image/png;base64,)

regex: /\*([^*]*)\**([^/*][^*]*\**)*/
